Good programming style and proper documentation make a program easy to read and help programmers prevent errors.

9.1. Appropriate Comments and Comment Styles
In addittion to line comments (beginning with //) and block comments (beginning with /*), javadoc comments begin with
 /** and end with */.
Use javadoc comments for commenting on an entire class or an entire method. For commenting on steps inside a method,
use line comments (//).

Liveexample: liveexample.pearsoncmg.com/javadoc/Exercise1.html.
It's corresponding java code is shown in liveexample.pearsoncmg.com/javadoc/Excercise1.txt

9.2. Proper Indentation an Spacing
Indentation is used to illustrate the structural relationships between a program's components or statements.

